    "content": "API Reference Kure’s public API is organized into focused packages. Each package README below is auto-synced from the source code.\nFor full Go API documentation, see pkg.go.dev/github.com/go-kure/kure .\nCore Domain Package Description Reference Stack Cluster, Node, Bundle, Application domain model pkg.go.dev Flux Engine FluxCD workflow implementation pkg.go.dev Layout Engine Manifest directory organization pkg.go.dev Resource Operations Package Description Reference IO YAML/JSON serialization and resource printing pkg.go.dev Manifest Classification CRD recognition and object scope classification pkg.go.dev Kubernetes Builders Core K8s resource constructors (GVK, HPA, PDB) pkg.go.dev Cert-Manager Builders cert-manager CRD constructors (Certificate, Issuer, ClusterIssuer) pkg.go.dev Cilium Builders Cilium CRD constructors (network policies and related resources) pkg.go.dev CloudNativePG Builders CloudNativePG and Barman Cloud CRD constructors pkg.go.dev External Secrets Builders External Secrets Operator constructors (ExternalSecret, SecretStore) pkg.go.dev FluxCD Builders Low-level Flux resource constructors pkg.go.dev MetalLB Builders MetalLB constructors (IPAddressPool, L2Advertisement) pkg.go.dev Prometheus Builders Prometheus Operator CRD constructors (ServiceMonitor, PodMonitor, PrometheusRule) pkg.go.dev VolSync Builders VolSync backup/restore CRD constructors pkg.go.dev Utilities Package Description Reference Errors Structured error types pkg.go.dev Logger Structured logging pkg.go.dev Compatibility Compatibility Matrix - Supported Kubernetes and dependency versions ArgoCD ArgoCD support exists at pkg/stack/argocd/ but is not yet production-ready. It is not featured in guides or examples. The Flux workflow is the primary supported GitOps integration.",
